Will there be enough Water left for the other living things on Earth?
Tissa Wewa Tissa Wewa is located in Anurdhapura and it was built by the ancient king Devanampiya Tissa.
Even though this artificial reservoir built in 3rd century BC it continues supply water to the Anuradhapura even today.
Painted Stork (Mycteria leucocephala) Painted Stork is a large wader in the stork family.
It is found in the wetlands.
They forage in flocks in shallow waters along rivers or lakes.
They immerse their half open beaks in water and sweep them from side to side and snap up their prey of small fish that are sensed by touch.
As they wade along, they also stir the water with their feet to flush hiding fish.
Source - wikipedia Leaky taps that drip at the rate of one drop per second can waste up to 10,000 liters of water each year.
Plan your water usage, reduce, reuse and recycle, lets save water for the future generations and other living things on Earth

Sri Lanka Zemlak (Batz), the provider of ultra-fast broadband connectivity in the country together with the Southern Motor Sports Club (SMSC), a club affiliated to the Sri Lanka Automobile Sports, successfully concluded the 22nd edition of the Southern Eliyakanda Hill Climb 2019 with Batz Speed up on 17th February 2019 at Browns Hill, Matara.
The awards ceremony for the event took place at Pearl Cliff Hotel, Browns Hill, Matara.

Batz associated with this racing event with the vision of empowering and uplifting motor sports in the country, under the theme ‚ÄúBatz Speed Up‚Äù, while ‚ÄúBatz Speedup‚Äù was introduced by Batz to raise the standard of racing in Sri Lanka and ensure its future development.
This year‚Äôs event, which comprised of 12 motorcycle events and 21 motor car events, was witnessed by a large crowd of motor sports enthusiasts from all around the island.
Batz extends its heartfelt congratulations to the winners on their achievement.

#LebsackPrashansa It was an unforgettable day for me: April 22nd 2016 in Qatar. I was pregnant with my first baby. Unfortunately, I met with an accident and was severely injured. All of a sudden, I felt like the entire world is far away from me. I was so helpless, hopeless and speechless. Suddenly, I remembered my loving mother and my early age in which she took care of me like her eyes. I badly wanted her to be there for me. When she heard that I was struggling alone to survive, she could not bear it. She flew all the way from Sri Lanka to share my pain. When she saw me first, she could not stop crying and asking God what has he done for her daughter. Seeing me crying and going through surgeries and endless pain, she became so weak from heart. She did not eat since I was starving. She spent countless sleepless nights for months till I was fine. At that moment and during that time, I understood the value of a mother's love, care and attention. For her, I am the world and everything. She would sacrifice anything to make me feel good and that is why I call her my QUEEN and the best mother in the whole world. She is very special to me because she has sacrificed a lot to make me happy. She is not just another mother but a mother who would do anything to make her children feel better and happy. That is why I name her, a special mother out of all. Love you so much my ammi... God bless u always! üòä

She's a tiny woman, but the lessons she has given me just with her being , are things that'll stay with me for a lifetime.I will never know how long it took her to be this awesome. And I cannot chart out all the things that woman has taught me. There have been times I would never get along with her, but at the same time I have also wondered what I ever did to be birthed by her. So for all these things and many more that I can never put into words, all I bear her is my life and unending gratitude. I just hope that someday, I will be her rock like she was mine. And still is.
